  "text": "All patients in the RME group were treated with acrylic bonded appliances ( Figure 1 ). In the ARME group, patients were treated with modified acrylic bonded appliances, which were built by adding an occlusal-lock mechanism on the nonaffected side ( Figure 2 ). The occlusal-lock mechanism on the nonaffected side was designed so that the vestibular surface of the appliance extended to the middle third of the mandibular teeth, and the inner surface of the appliance extended along the lingual surface of the mandibular teeth vertically. [CITATION_1] In both appliances, a hyrax screw (Dentaurum, Pforzheim, Germany) was placed in the acrylic plate parallel to the first molars and as close to the palate as possible. After occlusal adjustments were made, the appliances were bonded. The expansion protocol consisted of turning the screw twice every day for the first week and then turning once Angle Orthodontist, Vol 00, No 00, 0000 a day until a slight overcorrection of the crossbite was achieved. The screw was stabilized in both groups, and the occlusal lock was removed in the ARME group during the retention period. The appliances were left in place passively for 3 months.",
