      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "The occlusal-lock mechanism on the nonaffected side was designed so that the vestibular surface of the appliance extended to the middle third of the mandibular teeth, and the inner surface of the appliance extended along the lingual surface of the mandibular teeth vertically. In both appliances, a hyrax screw (Dentaurum, Pforzheim, Germany) was placed in the acrylic plate parallel to the first molars and as close to the palate as possible."
